In this letter, President Barack Obama informs the Speaker of the House about the deployment of U.S. forces to Jordan. The initial deployment was for a training exercise, but at the request of the Jordanian government, approximately 700 combat-equipped forces remained in Jordan after the exercise concluded. This detachment includes Patriot missile systems, fighter aircraft, and related support personnel. The purpose of their presence is to support Jordan's security and promote regional stability. The President asserts that this deployment is in line with U.S. national security and foreign policy interests. He provides this report to Congress in accordance with the War Powers Resolution.